  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does range hood repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most range hood repairs run between $100 and $280. A fan motor, blower wheel, light socket, or switch replacement is toward the lower end. Control board replacement on premium hoods like Wolf, Zephyr, or Vent-A-Hood runs higher. We provide a written estimate before any work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My range hood fan runs but doesn't seem to clear smoke — is it broken?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Not necessarily. There are two common explanations. First: a clogged grease filter dramatically reduces airflow — a filter that hasn't been cleaned in months can restrict CFM by 50% or more, making the fan seem weak when it's actually working fine. Second: if you have a high-BTU professional range (Wolf, Thermador, BlueStar), your hood may simply be underpowered for the burners. A 30,000 BTU burner on a Wolf requires significantly more CFM than a standard residential hood provides. We assess both when you call."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often should I clean my range hood filters?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Grease filters should be cleaned every 1–3 months depending on how much you cook. In LA, where people cook at home frequently and often with high-BTU professional ranges, monthly cleaning is not excessive. Most metal mesh filters can go in the dishwasher. Charcoal filters on ductless/recirculating hoods need replacing every 3–6 months — they can't be cleaned, only replaced. A saturated grease filter is both a fire hazard and the most common cause of perceived performance loss."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the difference between a vented and ventless range hood?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A vented range hood draws air through a grease filter and exhausts it outside through ductwork — this removes smoke, moisture, heat, and cooking odors from the kitchen entirely. A ventless or recirculating hood draws air through a grease filter and a charcoal filter, then recirculates the cleaned air back into the kitchen — it removes grease and some odors but not moisture or heat. Vented is significantly more effective and preferred for serious cooking. Ventless is the only option in many apartments and condos without ducting."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair high-end range hoods like Wolf, Vent-A-Hood, and Zephyr?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Wolf, Vent-A-Hood, Zephyr, Hestan, and Miele are among the premium hood brands we service most in LA. These units have different motor assemblies and control systems than consumer-grade hoods. We source OEM parts for Wolf specifically and carry parts for Zephyr and Broan. For Vent-A-Hood and Hestan, parts are sourced from authorized distributors."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My range hood is making a loud noise — what's wrong?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A rattling or vibrating noise often means the blower wheel has accumulated grease buildup and is now unbalanced, or a small object has gotten into the blower housing. A grinding or squealing sound indicates the fan motor bearings are failing. Both are repairable. The blower wheel is a separate component from the motor — we check both before recommending replacement of either."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the 90-day warranty cover on range hood repairs?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every range hood repair we complete carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

