<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01 — About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Before we diagnose a broken part — we check the filter.</h2>

        <p>A clogged grease filter is the most common reason an LA homeowner calls us about a "broken" range hood. A filter that hasn't been cleaned in three months can restrict airflow by 50% or more — the fan runs, the motor is fine, but the hood barely pulls air because nothing can get through the filter. We check the filter before concluding anything else is wrong. In many cases that's the whole call.</p>

        <p>The second thing we check for in LA kitchens specifically: CFM-to-BTU mismatch. Los Angeles has more Wolf, Thermador, and BlueStar professional ranges per household than almost any other city in the country. A Wolf range with 30,000–60,000 BTU burners requires significantly more ventilation capacity than a standard residential range hood provides. When a hood "doesn't seem to work" over a high-BTU professional range, the hood may be functioning correctly — it's just undersized for the job. That's not a repair, it's a replacement or upgrade conversation, and we'll have it honestly.</p>

        <p>When there is an actual mechanical failure — fan motor seized, blower wheel unbalanced with grease buildup, control board failed, lights dead — we carry parts for the brands common in LA and can usually complete same-visit.</p>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <div class="tip-label">🧹 Clean Your Filter First</div>
          <p>If your hood seems weak but the fan is running, pull out the metal mesh grease filter and hold it up to the light. If you can't see through it, cleaning it may restore full performance without any repair needed. Most metal filters can go in the dishwasher on the hottest cycle. Charcoal filters on ductless hoods can't be cleaned — they need replacement every 3–6 months. We carry both types.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
        <div class="cta-label">Same Day Range Hood Repair</div>
